        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Paleolithic [300019258], Stone Age [300106724], three-age system [300106723], styles, periods, and cultures by general era [300111078], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the transitional phase between Paleolithic and Neolithic cultures. The concept differs from Mesolithic in that it generally is applied particularly to the culture in eastern Europe, and stresses the continuity with processes begun earlier rather than distinct innovations that developed during this period.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a la fase de transición entre las culturas del Paleolítico y el Neolítico. El concepto difiere del Mesolítico, en que generalmente es aplicado en particular a las culturas de Europa Oriental y presiona la continuidad con los procesos comenzados anteriormente, prefiriendo las distintas innovaciones desarrolladas durante este período.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een overgangsfase tussen paleolithische en neolithische culturen. Dit concept verschilt van ‘mesolithisch’ doordat het meestal wordt toegespitst op de cultuur in het oosten van Europa en veeleer de nadruk legt op de continuïteit van eerder begonnen processen dan op uitgesproken vernieuwingen die zich in deze periode hebben ontwikkeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指舊石器時代和新石器時代之間的過渡階段，與中石器時代概念不同之處在於，通常此一名稱特別適用於東歐地區的文化，強調先前過程的延續性，而非這個時代所發展的顯著革新。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
